Input.sentence1: Because of the EAC atresia the tympanic membrane is absent and consequently the handle of the malleus is foreshortened and thickened.

Input.example_normal_1_2: The head of the malleus is patent.

Input.example_abnormal_1_2: The ossicles appear abnormal in orientation with apparent fusion of the malleus and incus to each other as well as with the wall of middle ear cavity.

Input.twoBefore2: The remainder of the middle ear shows abnormal opacification of the mesotympanum and hypotympanum and partial opacification of the attic. Again noted is poor pneumatization of the mastoid air cell complex.

Input.sentence3: The anterosuperior portion of the head of the malleus may be attached to the roof of the tympanic cavity or may be abutting it.
Input.twoBefore3: There is a small osseous discontinuity in the atretic plate. Because of the EAC atresia the tympanic membrane is absent and consequently the handle of the malleus is foreshortened and thickened.
Input.twoAfter3: The incus and the stapes appear normal. Cranial nerve VII appears to be in a normal position.
Input.example_normal_3_2: The external canal is clear and the tympanic membrane is patent.
Input.example_abnormal_3_1: The tympanic membrane is thickened.
Input.example_abnormal_3_2: The external auditory canal is atretic as well as the tympanic membrane.

Keywords: sentence classification nlp radiology medical penn chop

Input.twoBefore1: The incus is incompletely visualized. There is no labyrinthine fistula.
Input.twoAfter1: The inner ear structures, including the semicircular canals, vestibule, and cochlea are unremarkable. The vestibular aqueduct is not enlarged.
Input.example_normal_1_2: The external canal is clear and the tympanic membrane is patent.
Input.example_abnormal_1_1: The tympanic membrane is thickened.
Input.example_abnormal_1_2: The external auditory canal is atretic as well as the tympanic membrane.
Input.sentence2: The inner ear structures, including the cochlea, semicircular canals and internal auditory canals are unremarkable.
Input.twoBefore2: No abnormal opacifications are noted. The mastoid air cell complex is clear.
Input.twoAfter2: The vascular structures are intact on the right. On the left, no pathology is noted.
Input.example_normal_2_1: On the right side, the external auditory canal is patent.
Input.example_normal_2_2: The internal auditory canal is unremarkable.
Input.example_abnormal_2_1: The right internal auditory canal is severely hypoplastic, but is patent.
Input.example_abnormal_2_2: The external auditory canal is atretic as well as the tympanic membrane.
Input.sentence3: There is mild prominence of the vestibules, unchanged.
Input.twoBefore3: The visualized major intracranial vessels appear patent. A suboccipital venous sinus, an anatomic variant, is seen on the right.
Input.twoAfter3: There is increased opacification of the paranasal sinuses. Fluid in the mastoid air cells has decreased.
Input.example_normal_3_2: The semicircular canal, vestibule, and internal auditory canal on the left are unremarkable.
Input.example_abnormal_3_1: The right vestibule is enlarged compared to the contralateral vestibule.
Input.example_abnormal_3_2: The right vestibule is enlarged.

Input.example_normal_1_2: The semicircular canals are patent.

Input.twoAfter2: There is abscence of a normal tympanic membrane. The descending portion of the facial canal is slightly more anterior in its course compared to the left side.
Input.example_normal_2_2: FINDINGS:  Inferior to the facial nerve in the region of the oval window, there is a tiny soft tissue mass abutting the footplate of the stapes without evidence of dehiscence.
Input.example_abnormal_2_1: IMPRESSION: Dysplastic appearing left incus and malleus, abnormal articulation between the incus and the malleus and absent stapes on the left.

Input.twoBefore3: Suboptimal study due to patient motion. 2.
Input.twoAfter3: 3. Dysmorphic left cochlea.

Input.example_normal_3_2: The internal auditory canal is unremarkable.

Keywords: sentence classification nlp radiology medical penn chop
Input.sentence1: Slight asymmetry with the right vestibule with a more globular appearance.
Input.twoBefore1: No definite abnormality is seen in the visualized portion of the brain parenchyma. There is trace mucosal thickening of paranasal sinuses  IMPRESSION:  Prominence of the right vestibular aqueduct.
Input.twoAfter1: Hyperintensity within inferior bilateral mastoid air cells. Please correlate clinically.
Input.example_normal_1_2: The semicircular canal, vestibule, and internal auditory canal on the left are unremarkable.
Input.example_abnormal_1_1: The right vestibule is enlarged compared to the contralateral vestibule.
Input.example_abnormal_1_2: The right vestibule is enlarged.
Input.sentence2: The vestibular aqueduct is not enlarged.
Input.twoBefore2: The vestibulo-cochlear nerves are seen and appear normal. The inner ear structures, including the semicircular canals, vestibule, and cochlea are unremarkable.
Input.twoAfter2: On the left side, the external auditory canal is patent. The middle ear cavity is clear.
Input.example_normal_2_2: The cochlea, vestibular aqueducts and vestibules are normal in appearance and configuration bilaterally.
Input.example_abnormal_2_1: Bilaterally enlarged vestibular aqueducts, see comments.
Input.example_abnormal_2_2: The vestibular aqueducts of the temporal bones, bilaterally, appear enlarged on the axial T2 images.
Input.sentence3: Hyperintensity within inferior bilateral mastoid air cells.
Input.twoBefore3: There is trace mucosal thickening of paranasal sinuses  IMPRESSION:  Prominence of the right vestibular aqueduct. Slight asymmetry with the right vestibule with a more globular appearance.
Input.twoAfter3: Please correlate clinically. END OF IMPRESSION:
Input.example_normal_3_1: The mastoid air cells are well-pneumatized and clear.
Input.example_normal_3_2: The mastoid air cells are patent.
Input.example_abnormal_3_1: Abnormal signal intensity in the left mastoid air cells, as described.
Input.example_abnormal_3_2: As previously seen the right mastoid air cells are under pneumatized.

Title: Radiology Report Sentence Classification: Normal or Abnormal?
Description: Given three sentences from radiology reports, classify each as containing a normal or abnormal observation.
Keywords: sentence classification nlp radiology medical penn chop
Input.sentence1: IMPRESSION:  No definite identification of the cochlear division of the vestibulocochlear nerve on the right side.
Input.twoBefore1: There is diffuse opacification of the bilateral mastoid air cells and middle ear cavities. No definite abnormality is seen in the visualized portion of the brain parenchyma.
Input.twoAfter1: Subtle hypointensity within the lateral aspect of the right internal auditory canal could represent a flow artifact, volume averaging of adjacent bone or possibly may represent a very hypoplastic right cochlear nerve which, if real, demonstrates abnormally lateral/distal branching off of the right vestibular nerve. The right internal auditory canal is slightly decreased in anteroposterior diameter relative to the left side.
Input.example_normal_1_2: The inner ear structures, including the semicircular canal, vestibule and cochlea are unremarkable.
Input.example_abnormal_1_1: The cochlea is mildly dysplastic with incomplete partition of middle and apical turn.
Input.example_abnormal_1_2: IMPRESSION:  Mild dysplasia of the cochlea bilaterally.
Input.sentence2: The incus and malleus are intact bilaterally.
Input.twoBefore2: The middle ear cavities are small bilaterally. The inner ear structures, including the lateral semicircular canals, vestibule, and cochlea are dysplastic bilaterally.
Input.twoAfter2: Inflammatory debris is seen in the region of the oval window on the right, less so on the left. The mastoid air cells are small and underpneumatized bilaterally.
Input.example_normal_2_1: A normal malleus and incus was identified bilaterally.
Input.example_normal_2_2: The head of the malleus is patent.
Input.example_abnormal_2_1: Normal tympanic membranes is not seen on the right and is absent on the left, and the left malleus is abnormal in morphology and orientation.
Input.example_abnormal_2_2: The ossicles appear abnormal in orientation with apparent fusion of the malleus and incus to each other as well as with the wall of middle ear cavity.
Input.sentence3: Subtle hypointensity within the lateral aspect of the right internal auditory canal could represent a flow artifact, volume averaging of adjacent bone or possibly may represent a very hypoplastic right cochlear nerve which, if real, demonstrates abnormally lateral/distal branching off of the right vestibular nerve.
Input.twoBefore3: No definite abnormality is seen in the visualized portion of the brain parenchyma. IMPRESSION:  No definite identification of the cochlear division of the vestibulocochlear nerve on the right side.
Input.twoAfter3: The right internal auditory canal is slightly decreased in anteroposterior diameter relative to the left side. END OF IMPRESSION:
Input.example_normal_3_1: On the right side, the external auditory canal is patent.
Input.example_normal_3_2: The internal auditory canal is unremarkable.
Input.example_abnormal_3_1: The right internal auditory canal is severely hypoplastic, but is patent.
Input.example_abnormal_3_2: The external auditory canal is atretic as well as the tympanic membrane.
